First release:
  Download and verify missing sources. Verify sources already existing. Report failures after all done.

	Verify Sources already exist.
		It will check /var/spool/sorcery to determine if the source files already exist, if so, it will verify the hash, if available.

	Download and verify missing sources.
		The user starts the program and it will use the yaml grimoire and download and verify the urls for all spells, putting missing sources
		into /var/spool/sorcery (mirror checking and updating)

	Report status.
		The software should generate a report of all the information it's collected. If not reported, assume good. If reported, include the
		reason it was reported.
